From Facebook to Attorney General
Mark went
Randi Zuckerberg, Brent Tworetzky & Dave Morin invite you to attend a reception in honor of Chris Kelly! Come support one of your own as he runs for California Attorney General!! We will be serving delicious food and wine! Menu includes: - Prosciutto wrapped figs with goat cheese - Crostini with mascarpone and hot smoked Scottish salmon - Crostini with our fried eggplant and ricotta salata - Gorgonzola stuffed polenta triangles - Arborio risotto arancini with snow peas and fresh mozzarella We'll also have yummy Pinot Grigio and Syrah, as well as non-alcoholic beverages! To RSVP TODAY or contribute to the campaign visit http://www.actblue.com/page/kellyfb Attend the event as a: Co-host: $5000 Sponsor: $1000 Friend: $500 Fan: $150 Poke: $75 For more information contact Michael Avila at 310-576-2217 or Michael@kelly2010.com **** Contributions made to this committee will be used to elect Chris Kelly to the office of Attorney General in 2010 and are not tax deductible as charitable contributions under IRS-162(e). Provisions of the CA Political Reform Act impose limits on the contributions allowable for statewide candidates. This request does not seek a contribution in excess of applicable limits or from prohibited sources. An individual, union, political action committee, association, committee, partnership, business or corporation may contribute a maximum of $6,500 to the committee per election, primary and general, for a total allowable contribution $13,000. A registered Small Contributor Committee may contribute a maximum of $12,900 to the committee per election, primary and general, for a total allowable contribution of $25,800. Contributions from foreign nationals are prohibited. Paid for by Kelly for Attorney General 2010

Official Digg Meet-up - San Francisco
Mark went
Please join the Digg team for good conversation and tasty libations at the first official Digg Meet-up! We'll be making a few announcements and raising a frosty pint together at the first of many gatherings that we're throwing in the United States and abroad. Mingle with fellow Diggers to the sounds of DJs Mancub (Space Cowboys) & Shissla (House of Lotus). It's free to attend, so kick off Web 2.0 Expo (You can register here: https://en.oreilly.com/webexsf2008/public/register) and come celebrate Earth Day with drink specials and great DJs for a fun evening. See you at Mighty!
